'''Express Entry''' is a system used by the [[Government of Canada|Canadian government]] to manage applications for [[Permanent residency in Canada|Canadian permanent residence]] through certain economic immigration programs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/corporate/publications-manuals/express-entry-system-immigrants.html|title=Express Entry System - Canada.ca|last=Canada|first=Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship|website=www.canada.ca|language=en|access-date=2018-10-10}}</ref> The Express Entry system is used to manage applications for skilled and qualified workers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/corporate/publications-manuals/express-entry-what-prospective-candidates-need-know.html|title=Express Entry: What prospective candidates need to know - Canada.ca|last=Canada|first=Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship|website=www.canada.ca|language=en|access-date=2018-10-10}}</ref> Express Entry is designed to facilitate the immigration of skilled workers to Canada "who are most likely to succeed economically."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/corporate/publications-manuals/express-entry-what-prospective-candidates-need-know.html|title=Express Entry: What prospective candidates need to know - Canada.ca|last=Canada|first=Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship|website=www.canada.ca|language=en|access-date=2018-10-10}}</ref> The system boasts efficient processing times, with 80% of applications processed in 6 months or less.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/corporate/publications-manuals/express-entry-system-immigrants.html|title=Express Entry System - Canada.ca|last=Canada|first=Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship|website=www.canada.ca|language=en|access-date=2018-10-10}}</ref>

Those who are eligible for one of the programs managed by Express Entry submit an entry and the Canadian government issues and successful candidates can submit an application for permanent residence.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/immigrate-canada/express-entry/submit-profile/respond-invitation.html|title=Submit an Express Entry profile: Respond to an invitation  - Canada.ca|last=Canada|first=Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship|website=www.canada.ca|language=en|access-date=2018-10-10}}</ref> A positive result on this application will grant the applicant, and their accompanying family members, Canadian permanent resident status.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/corporate/publications-manuals/express-entry-system-immigrants.html|title=Express Entry System - Canada.ca|last=Canada|first=Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship|website=www.canada.ca|language=en|access-date=2018-10-10}}</ref>

== Economic value versus "first-come first-served" ==
Express Entry replaced the original "first-come first-served" immigration selection system. Express Entry was expected to be more responsive to regional labour shortages.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Lotf Ali|first=Jan Ali|date=October 2014|title=Welcome to Canada? A Critical Review and Assessment of Canada’s Fast-Changing Immigration Policies|url=http://www.torontolip.org/Portals/0/Resources/Settlement%20Services/Welcome%20to%20Canada_A%20Critical%20Review%20of%20Changing%20Immigration%20Policies.pdf|journal=Ryerson Centre for Immigration & Settlement|volume=|pages=18|via=}}</ref> It systemically favours qualified immigrants by prioritising such individuals and avoids the arbitrary selections of the previous system which, in some cases, were based on a first come basis.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Ibbitson|first=John|date=December 2014|title=Bootstrap Immigrants: Assessing the Conservative Transformation of Canada's Immigration Policy|url=https://www.cigionline.org/publications/bootstrap-immigrants-assessing-conservative-transformation-canadas-immigration-policy|journal=Centre for International Governance Innovation|volume=|pages=6|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://money.cnn.com/2016/03/18/news/donald-trump-move-to-canada/index.html|title=Want to move to Canada? Here's what you need to know|last=Wattles|first=Jackie|date=18 March 2016|work=CNN Money|access-date=6 March 2018|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref> According to Colin Singer, an immigration lawyer, the ideal candidate for Express Entry is "someone in their 20s that's very proficient in one of Canada's official languages [English and French], and is highly educated, likely at a master's [degree] level."<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://money.cnn.com/2016/03/18/news/donald-trump-move-to-canada/index.html|title=Want to move to Canada? Here's what you need to know|last=Wattles|first=Jackie|date=18 March 2016|work=CNN Money|access-date=6 March 2018|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref>

Concerns have also been expressed about the Express Entry system. Morton Beiser and Harald Bauder (2014) of Ryerson University wrote "Canada’s once pathbreaking immigration policies are being transformed into a system that mainly serves employers, treating immigrants not as future citizens or members of Canadian communities and families but merely as convenient or cheap labour." Others{{Who|date=November 2018}} fear that Express Entry gives too much power to politicians and bureaucrats. Advocates of Express Entry claim that Express Entry can reduce the number of migrants who fail to get work by better fitting immigrants to existing jobs vacancies.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Ibbitson|first=John|date=December 2014|title=Bootstrap Immigrants: Assessing the Conservative Transformation of Canada's Immigration Policy|url=https://www.cigionline.org/publications/bootstrap-immigrants-assessing-conservative-transformation-canadas-immigration-policy|journal=Centre for International Governance Innovation|volume=|pages=6|via=}}</ref>

== The system ==
The total amount of immigrants invited depends on the quota the Canadian government has set for itself. For 2018 the quota set is 310,000 immigrants.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/3836805/340k-immigrants-per-year-by-2020-government-unveils-new-immigration-targets/|title=Canadian government wants 310,000 immigrants in 2018, 340,000 a year by 2020|last=Scotti|first=Monique|date=1 November 2017|work=Global News|access-date=6 March 2018|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref> This quota is then reached by skimming from the top of the express entry pool and inviting the highest ranking candidates. For example, on February 7, 2018, the quota was 3,000 immigrants.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cicnews.com/2018/02/new-express-entry-draw-invites-3000-candidates-to-apply-for-canadian-permanent-residence-0210224.html#gs.diYKa78|title=New Express Entry draw invites 3,000 candidates to apply for Canadian permanent residence|last=Smith, Katem and Turner|first=Stephen Eman and Noah|date=21 February 2018|work=CANADA IMMIGRATION NEWSLETTER|access-date=5 March 2018|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref> Thus the top-ranked 3,000 individuals were invited. In the past{{When|date=November 2018}} the government has repeated this draw multiple times per year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/immigrate-canada/express-entry/become-candidate/rounds-invitations/results-previous.html|title=Express Entry results: Previous rounds of invitations|last=|first=|date=|website=www.canada.ca|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>

