'''''Jamaica Anansi Stories''''' is a book by [[Martha Warren Beckwith]] published in 1924.  It is a collection of [[folklore]], [[riddles]] and [[Transcription (music)|transcription]]s of [[folk music]], all involving the [[trickster]] [[Anansi]], gathered from [[Jamaica]]ns of [[Africa]]n descent.

